               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Filkǝsyos, Book of Philoxenus of Mabbogh: 250 questions and answers
                     (fols. 3r-121ra)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-4.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The text consists of a series of questions asked by monks (beginning
                        with ይቤሉ: አኃው) and answers given by an “interpreter” (starting with ይቤ:
                        መተርጕም). The questions are numbered.</note>
                     <note>- Traces of the original division of the text into ክፍል “part” on <locus target="#19rb">19rb</locus> (“chapter two”) and 31rb (“chapter
                        four”).</note>
                  </msItem>
